"a.无趣的，乏味的 【英】 adj. 无趣的,乏味的(unint eresting, dull) 【考】 反义词：entrancing( 使人入神的) adj. 无聊的, 令人厌烦的, 单调沉闷的 = uninteresting = dull; n 钻(孔) 【例】I had expected the book to be boring 我本以为这本书很乏味. 【反】entrancing(adj 使人神魂颠倒的, 使人入神的) 【记】bore 厌烦 + ing；音：拔 + ring 电话，拔电话号码是很烦的，现在电话号码越来越长 boring (adj.)  mid-15c., ""action of piercing,"" from bore (v.). From 1853 in reference to animals that bore; 1840 in the sense ""wearying, causing ennui."""
